480. quid eum? ‘what about him?' In conversational language an Acc. may be thus loosely used with no verb expressed and probably with none understood. One essential idea of the Acc is ‘limitation,’ and so an Ace. may be thus employed to limit the question to the person or thing spoken about. Cf. 755.
